.TH zola-build 1  "build " 
.SH NAME
zola\-build \- Deletes the output directory if there is one and builds the site
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBzola build\fR [\fB\-u\fR|\fB\-\-base\-url\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-drafts\fR] [\fB\-\-minify\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Deletes the output directory if there is one and builds the site
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-base\-url\fR \fI<BASE_URL>\fR
Force the base URL to be that value (defaults to the one in the config file)
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fI<OUTPUT_DIR>\fR
Outputs the generated site in the given path (by default \*(Aqpublic\*(Aq dir in project root)
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR
Force building the site even if output directory is non\-empty
.TP
\fB\-\-drafts\fR
Include drafts when loading the site
.TP
\fB\-\-minify\fR
Minify generated HTML files
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
